				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It was very difficult to prepare a top 10 list for South America. Each country even each city has its charm and beauty. It would have been much easier to prepare a top 20 but I took up the challenge. I hope this list helps people while choosing their destinations when they don’t have much time to visit the whole South America.</p>
<h6>1. Galapagos  Islands</h6>
<p>Let’s follow the footsteps of Charles Darwin and enjoy nature, sea, fishes, sea lions, giant tortoises and varieties of birds.</p>
<p><a title="Galapagos" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/714/23251186896_979cbfff34_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Galapagos" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/714/23251186896_979cbfff34_o.jpg" alt="Galapagos" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Galapagos" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/679/23277297555_f058e9ba4a_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Galapagos" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/679/23277297555_f058e9ba4a_o.jpg" alt="Galapagos" width="1280" height="853" /></a></p>
<h6>2. Salar de Uyuni</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a title="Salar de Uyuni" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/748/22649362353_437e3f8305_o.jpg" rel=""><span style="color: #000000;">3 days were definitely not enough. Not just the Salar but also all the lakes around, colourful mountains, the desert of Dali, the cemetery of trains. All of it is amazing</span>.<br />
</a><a title="Salar de Uyuni" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5670/22908552269_12dfee6021_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Salar de Uyuni" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5670/22908552269_12dfee6021_o.jpg" alt="Salar de Uyuni" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Salar de Uyuni" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/646/22649419603_1b5e40f875_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Salar de Uyuni" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/646/22649419603_1b5e40f875_o.jpg" alt="Salar de Uyuni" width="1280" height="853" /></a></p>
<h6>3. Waterfalls of Iguazu</h6>
<p>You can enjoy them closely from Argentina and have a wonderful panoramic view from Brazil. They are so big, that you will feel pretty small.</p>
<h6><a title="Iguazu" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5623/22877139039_bacd4bdd97_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Iguazu" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5623/22877139039_bacd4bdd97_o.jpg" alt="Iguazu" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Iguazu" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5694/23245091995_48176f7098_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Iguazu" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5694/23245091995_48176f7098_o.jpg" alt="Iguazu" width="1280" height="853" /></a>4. Perito Moreno</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a title="Perito Moreno" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5763/23275417395_ec2a81efd4_o.jpg" rel=""><span style="color: #000000;">Even though I heard before going that it is immense, I couldn’t imagine the size until I saw it with my own eyes. They rise 70 meters above the sea level.  You will be fascinated.</span><br />
</a><a title="Perito Moreno" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5635/22907481799_3e6a8d7ffa_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Perito Moreno" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5635/22907481799_3e6a8d7ffa_o.jpg" alt="Perito Moreno" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Perito Moreno" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5748/23249513456_35bd022ee8_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Perito Moreno" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5748/23249513456_35bd022ee8_o.jpg" alt="Perito Moreno" width="1280" height="853" /></a></p>
<h6>5. Trekking of Santa Cruz</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Trekking lovers will have 4 days without all kind of technology and experience extreme changes of climate. You can fully enjoy mountains during the day and the stars during the night.</p>
<p><a title="Santa Cruz" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5819/23249853106_15280ee76d_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Santa Cruz" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5819/23249853106_15280ee76d_o.jpg" alt="Santa Cruz" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Santa Cruz" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/670/22647565814_494891d51c_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Santa Cruz" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/670/22647565814_494891d51c_o.jpg" alt="Santa Cruz" width="1280" height="853" /></a></p>
<h6>6. Torres del Paine</h6>
<p>Another awesome trek in the Chilean Patagonia with awesome views. Unfortunately some parts of the park are burned down but still the beauty remained.</p>
<h6><a title="Torres del Paine" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5808/22907674649_b262db15ea_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Torres del Paine" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5808/22907674649_b262db15ea_o.jpg" alt="Torres del Paine" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Torres del Paine" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/676/22907690939_f4ebb29147_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Torres del Paine" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/676/22907690939_f4ebb29147_o.jpg" alt="Torres del Paine" width="1280" height="853" /></a>7. Cuzco and Machu Pichhu</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In Cuzco you can easily picture yourself in the past wandering through houses and streets built with Inka stones. And Machu Picchu…it doesn’t matter how many photos you have seen of it, you will still get shocked and amazed.</p>
<p><a title="Cuzco" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/634/23168172792_6a55a36d5d_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Cuzco" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/634/23168172792_6a55a36d5d_o.jpg" alt="Cuzco" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Machu Picchu" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5655/22882228787_b3353303c4_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Machu Picchu" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5655/22882228787_b3353303c4_o.jpg" alt="Machu Picchu" width="683" height="1024" /></a></p>
<h6>8. Trekking of Ciudad Perdida</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;">You will dance with mud, dance with rain and dance with rivers all throughout the jungle until you reach your well-deserved destination: The Lost City.</p>
<h6><a title="Ciudad Perdida" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5643/22650322983_d52d95669f_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Ciudad Perdida" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5643/22650322983_d52d95669f_o.jpg" alt="Ciudad Perdida" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Ciudad Perdida" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5628/22649036764_a6f370b389_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Ciudad Perdida" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5628/22649036764_a6f370b389_o.jpg" alt="Ciudad Perdida" width="1280" height="853" /></a>9. Rio de Janeiro</h6>
<p>Gorgeous kilometric beaches with mountains surrounding them, forest in the background, favelas and lovely, friendly Brazilians.</p>
<h6><a title="Rio de Janeiro" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/702/22876378099_c3cccd7e2f_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Rio de Janeiro" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/702/22876378099_c3cccd7e2f_o.jpg" alt="Rio de Janeiro" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Rio de Janeiro" href="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5629/22876402879_b62ff84304_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Rio de Janeiro" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5629/22876402879_b62ff84304_o.jpg" alt="Rio de Janeiro" width="1280" height="853" /></a>10. Cartagena de Indias</h6>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Colourful colonial buildings, stylish restaurants and cafes, salsa and joyful people.</p>
<p><a title="Cartagena de Indias" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/651/23194862841_24b0385d32_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Cartagena de Indias" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/651/23194862841_24b0385d32_o.jpg" alt="Cartagena de Indias" width="1280" height="853" /></a><a title="Cartagena de Indias" href="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/746/22909533379_18fa0dcc3c_o.jpg" rel=""><img class="aligncenter" title="Cartagena de Indias" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/746/22909533379_18fa0dcc3c_o.jpg" alt="Cartagena de Indias" width="1280" height="853" /></a></p>
